cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.SD 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with dialogue generation and natural language processing. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a technique to improve the performance of neural dialogue agents. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses memory networks, a type of neural network, to encode knowledge. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the paper proposes a technique to improve the training of neural networks. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a technique to improve the performance of software agents.
